  "texts": [
    "In the context of SLR, these methodologies are predominantly utilised to semi-automate tasks like screening and data extraction (Cowie et al. 2022; Burgard and Bittermann 2023).",
    "The SLR methodology consists of six distinct stages (Keele et al. 2007; Higgins 2011): (i) Planning, (ii) Search, (iii) Screening, (iv) Data Extraction and Synthesis, (v) Quality Assessment, and (vi) Reporting.",
    "Each stage plays a pivotal role in ensuring the comprehensiveness and rigour of the review process.",
    "The planning phase is foundational to the entire review process, as it involves formulating a set of precise and specific research questions that the SLR seeks to address (O 'Connor et al. 2008).",
    "A detailed protocol is also developed during this stage, outlining the appropriate methodologies that will be adopted to carry out the review (Fontaine et al. 2022)."
  ],
